1. Repair locale (add LC_ALL and LANGUAGE in system environment):
    hints for nano:
        save: Ctrl + O
        exit: Ctrl + X

    nano /etc/environment

    insert two lines at the end of file:
        LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8
        LANG=en_US.UTF-8

2. Exit and reenter server
3. Update system:
    apt-get update
    apt-get -y upgrade

4. Install server environment
    apt-get install nginx-full
    apt-get install redis-server
    apt-get install postgresql
    apt-get install python-dev python-virtualenv
    apt-get install libpq-dev

5. Clone git repo:
    cd /var/www/
    git clone https://github.com/codemeetspeople/bcw6.git

6. Install Python packages manager:
    apt-get install python-pip

7. Create python environment:
    hint:
        activate virtualenv: source /var/www/bcw6/venv/bin/activate
        deactivate virtualenv: deactivate

    cd /var/www/bcw6/
    virtualenv venv
    source venv/bin/activate
    pip install -r .meta/packages

8. Modify postgresql config:
    nano /etc/postgresql/9.5/main/pg_hba.conf

    replace string:
        # "local" is for Unix domain socket connections only
        local   all             all                                     peer

    with:
        # "local" is for Unix domain socket connections only
        local   all             all                                     md5

    service postgresql restart

9. Create database
    sudo -u postgres psql
    
    in psql console:
    CREATE ROLE bcw6 LOGIN CREATEDB ENCRYPTED PASSWORD 'bcw6';
    CREATE DATABASE bcw6 WITH OWNER=bcw6 ENCODING='UTF8';









